snippet.textDisplay:
Bosa must have reminded the O Lineman of his old teddy bear as he’s holding onto Bosa with dear life just after point of contact till the very end of the play.This happened right in front of the ref who was just behind Mahomes during the play. That was one of at least 10 non holding calls the Chief’s oline didn’t incur throughout the game but of course of the most pivotal, not to mention one of overwhelmingly obvious non calls; the tackle couldn’t stop Bosa without holding him the entire game.

The refs were just awful and really there were tons of non-calls and bad calls that gave the Chiefs this game. Disgusting display of yet again the refs deciding the outcome of a game. Never mind the two late hits on Garoppolo in the last 7 minutes that weren’t called, this non call against the tackle was utter BS and as obvious as day light, and there’s no doubt Mahomes would’ve been sacked had Bosa not gotten held.
